MPs will tomorrow begin to debate the approval of Chief Justice nominee David Maraga.National Assembly's decision to concur with the Justice and Legal Affairs committee endorsing Maraga to head the Supreme Court will see him succeed the retired Willy Mutunga. The committee chaired by Ainabkoi MP Samuel Chepkonga vetted Maraga on Thursday but asked the House for more time write and table the report.The committee during its vetting thrashed three petitions challenging Maraga's nomination.The Chepkonga led committee unanimously endorsed Maraga for appointment after an intensive two-hour interview.The House is expected to receive the name of deputy Chief Justice nominee Philomena Mwilu from the President this week. Judicial Service Commission nominated Mwilu for the position last Monday out of 12 candidates.